  "text": "TEM Acquisition and Image Analysis. A small amount of product was dissolved in water (PEG-grafted NPs) or toluene (assynthesized NPs) and dropped onto a TEM-grid (3.05 mm HR-TEMgrid, copper 300 mesh, carbon film). TEM images were obtained using a FEI Tecnai G2 200 kV transmission electron microscope at 200 kV. Core diameters were evaluated using the Pebbles software package [CITATION_1] with a local intensity fitting algorithm. For this analysis, about 1000 particles were sampled by Pebbles.",
